16 fluency, conceptual understanding, and productive dispositions. A
17 screening instrument approved by the State Board of Education
18 pursuant to the provisions of Section 1210.508C of this title shall
19 be utilized for the purposes of this section. In determining which
20 screening instrument to approve, the State Board of Education shall
21 take into consideration, at a minimum, the following factors:
22 1. The time required to conduct the screening instrument with
23 the intention of minimizing the impact on instructional time;
24
