14 follows:
15 Section 1210.907. A. Beginning with the 2026-2027 2027-2028
16 school year and for each school year thereafter, any student
17 enrolled in second, third, fourth, and fifth grade in a public
18 school in this state who is assessed through the Oklahoma Math
19 Achievement and Proficiency Act pursuant to Section 3 1210.901 of
20 this act title, and who is not meeting grade-level targets in
21 mathematics after the beginning-of-the-year screening instrument,
22 shall be screened for dyscalculia. Screening also may be requested
23 for a student by his or her parent or legal guardian, teacher, or
24 counselor. A student who is identified with characteristics of
Req. No. 17365 Page 31

1 dysc alculia shall not be required to be rescreened unless requested
2 by his or her parent or legal guardian. Nothing in this section
3 shall preclude a school district from administering a dyscalculia
4 screening tool to identify, refer, evaluate, or provide appropriate
5 services to any student suspected of having dyscalculia or another
6 math-related disorder prior to the 2027-2028 school year.
7 B. No later than December 31, 2025 February 28, 2027, the State
8 Board of Education, in consultation with the Office of Mathematics
9 Improvement within the State Department of Education, shall develop
10 policies for dyscalculia screening required pursuant to this section
11 and shall include, but not be limited to:
12 1. The definition and characteristics of dyscalculia and
13 related disorders;
14 2. The process for referring students in grades two through
15 five for screening;
16 3. A process for providing notification to parents or legal
17 guardians of the use of a qualified dyscalculia-screening
18 dyscalculia screening tool and notification of the results of the
19 screening;
20 4. A process for providing the parents or legal guardians of
21 students screened for dyscalculia with information and resource
22 material regarding dyscalculia;
23
24
